            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18330411-205-person1573">
                  HENRY 
                  FRANCIS BEVERLY
               <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1573" type="surname" value="FRANCIS BEVERLY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1573" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1573" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I lodge in <placeName id="t18330411-205-crimeloc1160">West-street, College-street, Camden-town</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18330411-205-crimeloc1160" type="placeName" value="West-street, College-street, Camden-town"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18330411-205-crimeloc1160" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18330411-205-off1158 t18330411-205-crimeloc1160"></join>. The prisoner lodged in the same house - I left town the beginning of January, and left the prisoner there; after my return I missed these articles- I had taken the coat with me into the country, and brought it back; the prisoner still lodged in the same house - I missed the coat about the 3rd of April; I was not aware that I had lost either the shirt or the trousers, till the duplicate was found.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18330411-205-person1574">
                  HANNAH 
                  DIXON
               <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1574" type="surname" value="DIXON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1574" type="given" value="HANNAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1574" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live servant at the house. I made the prisoner's bed on Monday last, and found in it a purse with seventeen duplicates - I told my master of it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Did I not leave my room in the morning? and is not the door open? A. Yes, another person might have gone in; I did not know who the purse belonged to.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18330411-205-person1575">
                  RICHARD 
                  WARNE
               <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1575" type="surname" value="WARNE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1575" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1575" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a carpenter, and occupy the house in College-street, where the prisoner and prosecutor lodged; on Monday last Dixon gave me the duplicates.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. You knew where I worked, and knew my father? A. Yes; you have lodged there six months.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18330411-205-person1576">
                  WILLIAM 
                  CASSEL
               <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1576" type="surname" value="CASSEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1576" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1576" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker, and live in Camden-town. I have a shirt, pawned by a man who gave the name of John Brown, No. 5, Camden-street - I gave him this duplicate.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18330411-205-person1577">
                  JAMES 
                  MOODY
               <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1577" type="surname" value="MOODY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1577" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1577" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker, and live in East-street, Marylebone. This coat was pawned with me by the prisoner for 7s. in the name of George Allen; I gave him this duplicate - it was on Wednesday evening, the 3rd of April, between eight and nine o'clock.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Did you not say, when I was at the lockup place, that you believed I was not the person who pawned it? A. No, I did not; you are the person.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18330411-205-person1578">
                  ROBERT 
                  HAWKLEY
               <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1578" type="surname" value="HAWKLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1578" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1578" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (Police-serjeant S 1.) I went to the Bell and Crown, Camden-town, last Tuesday night week - I found the prisoner in bed: I awoke him, and asked if his name was not 
               <persName id="t18330411-205-person1579">
                  William 
                  Oliver
               <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1579" type="surname" value="Oliver"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1579" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1579" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             - he opened his eyes, and said No: I took the candle to him, and said, "I am sure you are the man whom I want, for stealing a great coat, and some other articles:" he said, "Never mind, let it be till morning" - I made him get up and dress; I found a note in one of his pockets - I received these duplicates at his lodging.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. I made no resistance? A. No, you did not.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18330411-205-person1580">
                  RICHARD 
                  WILCOX FAIRLAM
               <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1580" type="surname" value="WILCOX FAIRLAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1580" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330411-205-person1580" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker. I have a pair of trousers, pawned on the 8th of February for 3s. - I do not know by whom, but I gave this duplicate which was found in the purse.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I slept in the back parlour; this gentleman has the front parlour and first floor - I heard of the duplicates being found in my bed, and I was persuaded to sleep out, at the Bell and Crown, not more than one hundred yards from the house.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18330411-205-verdict1161" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18330411-205-verdict1161" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 22. - <rs id="t18330411-205-punish1162" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18330411-205-punish1162" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18330411-205-defend1570 t18330411-205-punish1162"></join>
               Transported for Seven Years
            </rs>.</p>
